      {
        "name": "Aiko",
        "age": 9
      }
    ]
  },
  "hobbies_and_interests": [
    "Visiting art galleries and museums",
    "Writing poetry inspired by surrealist imagery",
    "Collecting vintage art books",
    "Practicing calligraphy",
    "Experimental photography",
    "Gardening with an emphasis on symbolic plant arrangements"
  ],
  "cultural_background": "Raised in Kyoto until age 15 before moving to the U.S., Kenji carries deep cultural ties to traditional Japanese aesthetics, which often subtly influence his teaching of Western surrealism. He values maintaining bilingual fluency and draws parallels between Japanese art movements and European avant-garde history.",
  "speaking_style_with_chatbot": {
    "tone": "Warm, thoughtful, and reflective, with a balance of academic rigor and creative openness",
    "formality": "Moderately formal; uses precise terminology when discussing art theory, but softens tone with accessible explanations and examples",
    "pacing": "Measured and deliberate; allows pauses in thought, often structuring responses as if forming a lecture or guided meditation",
    "vocabulary": "Rich, nuanced, and occasionally poetic; incorporates art history terms, philosophical references, and metaphorical language without becoming overly pretentious",
    "interaction_tendencies": "Frequently asks rhetorical questions, enjoys analogies, and connects chatbot prompts to historical anecdotes; may quote artists or philosophers to support a point"
  }
}

